# Supabase Edge Functions Environment Variables
#
# This file documents all environment variables used by Edge Functions.
# For local development, set these as environment variables before running `supabase start`.
# For production, use `supabase secrets set` to configure these values.
#
# Copy this file to .env.local (or similar) and fill in your actual values.
# DO NOT commit .env.local or any file with actual secrets to version control.
#
# To use: Rename this file to .env.example

# ============================================================================
# Required: GitHub App Configuration
# ============================================================================

# GitHub App ID from your GitHub App settings
# Find at: https://github.com/settings/apps/your-app-name
GITHUB_APP_ID=your_github_app_id_here

# GitHub App Client ID (OAuth client ID)
# Find at: https://github.com/settings/apps/your-app-name
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id_here

# GitHub App Client Secret (OAuth client secret)
# Find at: https://github.com/settings/apps/your-app-name
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_client_secret_here

# GitHub App Private Key (PEM format)
# Download from: https://github.com/settings/apps/your-app-name
# Should include -----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY----- and -----END PRIVATE KEY-----
# For multi-line values, you may need to use quotes or escape newlines
GITHUB_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
your_private_key_content_here
-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"

# ============================================================================
# Required: JWT Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Secret for JWT token signing and validation
# Must be at least 32 characters long
# Generate a secure random secret using: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=your_secure_random_jwt_secret_minimum_32_characters_long

# ============================================================================
# Optional: CORS Configuration
# ============================================================================

# Comma-separated list of allowed origins
# Examples:
#   - Single origin: http://localhost:3000
#   - Multiple origins: http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173
#   - Wildcard (not recommended with credentials): *
# Default: "*"
CORS_ALLOW_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173

# Enable credentials in CORS requests
# Set to "true" to allow cookies/credentials in cross-origin requests
# When true, CORS_ALLOW_ORIGIN cannot be "*" (browsers will reject)
# Default: "false"
CORS_ALLOW_CREDENTIALS=true

# Comma-separated list of allowed headers
# Default: "authorization, x-client-info, apikey, content-type"
# CORS_ALLOW_HEADERS=authorization, x-client-info, apikey, content-type

# Comma-separated list of allowed HTTP methods
# Default: "GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS"
# CORS_ALLOW_METHODS=GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS

# ============================================================================
# Local Development Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# For local development with `supabase start`:
# 1. Set these as environment variables in your shell:
#    export CORS_ALLOW_ORIGIN="http://localhost:3000"
#    export CORS_ALLOW_CREDENTIALS="true"
#    # ... etc
# 2. Then start Supabase: supabase start
#
# Or create a startup script that exports these variables before starting.
#
# ============================================================================
# Production Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# For production/remote Supabase:
# 1. Use `supabase secrets set` to configure:
#    supabase secrets set GITHUB_APP_ID=your_app_id
#    supabase secrets set CORS_ALLOW_ORIGIN=https://yourdomain.com
#    # ... etc
# 2. Secrets are automatically available to deployed Edge Functions
#
# ============================================================================

